#include <fstream>
#include <algorithm>

int main() {
    std::ifstream in("tort.in");
    std::ofstream out("tort.out");

    int M, N, L, portions;
    in >> M >> N;

    // Calculate the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) for M and N
    int a = M, b = N, t;
    while (b != 0) {
        t = b;
        b = a % b;
        a = t;
    }
    // The size of the square portion will be the GCD of M and N
    L = a;

    // Calculate the number of portions by dividing the area by the area of one portion
    portions = (M * N) / (L * L);
  
    out << portions << " " << L;
    
    // Close the file streams
    in.close();
    out.close();
    return 0;
}
```
This C++ program solves the challenge as specified. It reads the dimensions M and N from "tort.in", calculates the greatest common divisor (GCD) to find the size of the largest square portion L that can be used to divide the cake, computes the number of such portions, and finally writes the results to "tort.out".
